article.headline: Binghamton 62, New Hampshire 49
article.story: DURHAM, N.H. (AP) -- Ian Milne and Andre Heard scored 21 points each leading Binghamton to a 62-49 victory Thursday night over New Hampshire. Milne nailed five-of-six three-pointers and keyed an 18-2 second half run that turned a close game into a blowout. Clinging to a 36-32 lead early in the second half, Binghamton (4-9, 1-1 America east) hit five straight shots and held New Hampshire (2-11, 03) without a field goal for more than eight minutes. Milne's final three-pointer pushed the lead to 54-34 with 10:22 left, and Binghamton never looked back. Of Heard's 21 points, 16 came in the first half. Blagoj Janev was New Hampshire's only player to score in double figures, registering 12 points.
